content:
After clicking Execute, if writing to a file, first check if the code returned by the LLM seems truncated. Common patterns I've seen are:

* Rest of the file remains unchanged...
# Rest of the script contents...
// Rest of the function...
// ... (previous code remains unchanged)
// ... (rest of the function remains unchanged)
// ... (rest of the file remains unchanged)

If so, put up a confirm box saying that the code appears to be truncated, would you like to proceed. Also a note to remind LLL in prompt to show the full <filename>.
